{"title_page": "Otoboke Beaver", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name                = Otoboke Beaver<br />\u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\uff5e\u30d0\uff5e\n| image               = OtobokeBeaverNottinghamLive.jpg\n| caption             = Otoboke Beaver performing in Nottingham, 2016 (L-R: Hiro-Chan, Accorinrin, Pop [on drums], Yoyoyoshie)\n| image_size          =\n| background          = group_or_band\n| alias               =\n| origin              = [[Kyoto prefecture|Kyoto]], Japan\n| genre               = {{hlist|[[Hardcore punk]]|[[noise rock]]|[[alternative rock]]}}\n| years_active        = 2009&ndash;present\n| label               = [[Damnably]]\n| associated_acts     = \n| website             = https://otobokebeaver-kyoto.jimdo.com/\n| current_members     = Accorinrin<br />Yoyoyoshie<br />Hiro-Chan<br />Kahokiss\n| past_members        = Nishikawachi<br />Pop\n}}\n\n'''Otoboke Beaver''' (\u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\uff5e\u30d0\uff5e) is a [[punk rock]] band from [[Kyoto]], Japan. The band is named after a [[love hotel]] in [[Osaka]] near the high school of one of the band members.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mcmcomiccon.com|title=Our Websites|first=MCM Comic|last=Con|website=MCM Comic Con}}</ref> Musically, the band play a very fast-paced and aggressive style of punk-rock, with frequent changes in rhythm and tempo, accompanied by [[gang vocals]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vDzecXYy1D0|title=Otoboke Beaver \u2013 Okoshiyasu!! Otoboke Beaver [FULL ALBUM STREAM]|first=|last=Damnably|date=5 June 2016|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://louderthanwar.com/otoboke-beaver-pre-tour-interview-ep-review/|title=Otoboke Beaver - pre-tour interview and EP review|date=11 April 2016|publisher=}}</ref> Their songs feature love and relationships as regular themes, often based on singer Accorinrin's own experiences.<ref name=\"auto\"/><ref name=\"electricbloomwebzine.com\">[https://www.electricbloomwebzine.com/2016/05/otoboke-beaver-interview.html ]{{dead link|date=May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe band formed in 2009 while the members were active in the \"Rock Commune\" music club at [[Ritsumeikan University]] in [[Kyoto]].<ref>\n{{cite web|url=https://rooftop.cc/interview/190807130000.php|title=\u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\u301c\u30d0\u301c - \u5727\u5dfb\u306e\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6\u3067\u4e16\u754c\u3092\u9a5a\u304b\u305b\u308b\u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\u301c\u30d0\u301c\u3001\u307e\u3060\u307e\u3060\u9032\u5316\u4e2d\uff01 - \u30a4\u30f3\u30bf\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc (Band Interview in Japanese) - Rooftop Aug. 8, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.damnably.com/otoboke-beaver-%e3%81%8a%e3%81%a8%e3%81%bc%e3%81%91%e3%83%93%ef%bd%9e%e3%83%90%ef%bd%9e/|title=Otoboke Beaver - Damnably|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"electricbloomwebzine.com\"/> The original members were Accorinrin (guitar, vocals), Yoyoyoshie (guitar), Pop (drums), and Nishikawachi (bass). \n\nIn June 2011, Otoboke Beaver released a demo CD featuring three songs, including an early version of \"Chuchu Song,\" a live favorite that would be later re-recorded and distributed to supporters who helped fund the band's first trip to the United States. A mini-album followed in December of the same year. The cover art for both releases were designed by Yukari Matsuoka, and feature a distinctive cartoon of a nude woman with a rabbit's head.{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\nIn 2012 the group released their first live album through Egypt Records. In 2013 they released a limited-edition single through Jet Set Records, featuring the newly recorded \"Otobokebeaver Daijikenbo\" and two live tracks. In March of the same year, the band released the mini-album, ''Love Me Sign''. Bassist Nishikawachi left the band in 2013 and was replaced by Hiro-Chan, a fan who asked to join via e-mail.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://otobokebeaver-kyoto.jimdo.com/biography/|title=\ud83d\udc6f We Are Otoboke Beaver \ud83d\udc6f|website=Otoboke Beaver official web site}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.list.co.uk/article/89648-interview-otoboke-beaver-people-in-japan-perform-feelings-without-moving-bodies-but-people-in-uk-tell-us-directly/|title=Interview: Otoboke Beaver \u2013 'People in Japan perform feelings without moving bodies. But people in UK tell us directly.'|date=21 March 2017|website=The List}}</ref> \n\nOtoboke Beaver participated in [[Record Store Day|Record Store Day 2015]], releasing the single  \"Akimahenka\" on vinyl. In 2016, the band signed with UK-based label [[Damnably]]. The ''Okoshiyasu!! Otoboke Beaver'' compilation album was released, featuring the majority of the songs found on the group's first two mini-albums, with the addition of \"Akimahenka.\" The band recorded a live session for John Kennedy on [[XFM]] and toured the UK with [[Shonen Knife]] and Leggy. The EP ''Bakuro Book'' followed shortly thereafter, with another EP titled ''Love is Short!!'' appearing the following year for [[Record Store Day|Record Store Day 2017]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://otobokebeaver-kyoto.jimdo.com/discography/|title=\ud83d\udc6fDISCOGRAPHY\ud83d\udc6f|website=Otoboke Beaver official web site}}</ref> The song \"Love Is Short!!\" reached the UK singles chart.{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\nThe band began touring internationally in 2016, including dates at the 100 Club in London and [[South by Southwest|SXSW]] in the United States in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://schedule.sxsw.com/2017/events/MS37763|title=Otoboke Beaver \u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\uff5e\u30d0\uff5e|website=SXSW 2019 Schedule}}</ref> Their trip to SXSW was helped by fan-funding via Campfire and [[Kickstarter]] in order to help cover travel expenses.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://damnably.bandcamp.com/track/otoboke-beaver-chu-chu-song|title=Otoboke Beaver - Chu Chu Song, by Damnably|website=Damnably}}</ref> In 2018, the band traveled over 24,000 miles in one week to play two slots at the [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival|Coachella Festival]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fuse.tv/2018/01/coachella-2018-x-japan-otoboke-beaver-japanese-rock-diversity|title=Coachella 2018 Spotlights J-Rock With X Japan and Otoboke Beaver|first=|last=News|website=Fuse}}</ref> and a three-date headlining tour in the UK with label-mates [[Say Sue Me]] and Leggy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.damnably.com/2017/12/attyuuma-blink-of-an-eye-2018-tour-%e3%81%8a%e3%81%a8%e3%81%bc%e3%81%91%e3%83%93%ef%bd%9e%e3%83%90%ef%bd%9e%e3%80%80-otoboke-beaver-kyoto-japan-w-say-sue-me-busan-south-korea/|title=ATTYUUMA (Blink of an eye) 2018 Tour \u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\uff5e\u30d0\uff5e - Otoboke Beaver (Kyoto, Japan) w/ Say Sue Me (Busan, South Korea) & Leggy (USA) - Damnably|publisher=}}</ref> Other notable tour-mates have included [[The Cribs]], [[Miyavi]], [[Guitar Wolf]], and [[Wussy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.synclinks.co.uk/artist/ODIxNjgtMzdiNjZk/|title=Bucks Music Group - Otoboke Beaver|website=www.synclinks.co.uk}}</ref>\n\nThe album ''Okoshiyasu!! Otoboke Beaver'' was re-released on vinyl for [[Record Store Day]] in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://recordstoreday.co.uk/releases/rsd-2018/otoboke-beaver/|title=Otoboke Beaver - Record Store Day|website=recordstoreday.co.uk}}</ref> Also that year, founding drummer Pop announced her departure from the band.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://otobokebeaver.kyotolog.net/%E6%9C%AA%E9%81%B8%E6%8A%9E/%E3%81%8A%E3%81%A8%E3%81%BC%E3%81%91%E3%83%93%EF%BD%9E%E3%83%90%EF%BD%9E%E3%82%92%E5%BF%9C%E6%8F%B4%E3%81%97%E3%81%A6%E3%81%8F%E3%81%A0%E3%81%95%E3%81%A3%E3%81%A6%E3%81%84%E3%82%8B%E7%9A%86%E6%A7%98%E3%81%B8|title=\u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\uff5e\u30d0\uff5e\u306e\u304a\u3078\u3084 \u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\uff5e\u30d0\uff5e\u3092\u5fdc\u63f4\u3057\u3066\u304f\u3060\u3055\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u7686\u69d8\u3078|website=otobokebeaver.kyotolog.net}}</ref> Pop was replaced by Kahokiss, who had attended the same university music club as the band's founding members almost a decade before. In March 2019, Otoboke Beaver performed at SXSW in Austin, Texas.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://schedule.sxsw.com/2019/artists/2004502|title=Otoboke Beaver|website=SXSW 2019 Schedule|language=en|access-date=2019-03-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://jrock247.com/2019/02/asterism-ex-girl-otoboke-beaver-among-top-japanese-indie-acts-sxsw-2019/|title=ASTERISM, eX-GIRL, Otoboke Beaver among top Japanese indie acts at SXSW 2019|date=2019-02-21|website=JRock247|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-16}}</ref> The album ''[[Itekoma Hits]]'', featuring new songs and compiling some previously-released singles, was released by Damnably in April 2019.\n\n==Response==\nOtoboke Beaver's fun yet frenetic sound and raucous live performances have garnered them praise from the likes of ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/19162-otoboke-beaver-love-is-short/|title=Listen to 'Love Is Short' by Otoboke Beaver|publisher=|via=pitchfork.com}}</ref> [[NPR]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2017/04/21/524864227/japanese-punks-otoboke-beaver-take-revenge-in-a-grindhouse-inspired-video|title=Japanese Punks Otoboke Beaver Take Revenge In A Grindhouse-Inspired Video|website=NPR.org}}</ref> [[The Fader|The Fader,]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2017/03/29/otoboke-beaver-sil-vous-plait-video|title=Watch Outrageously Cool Japanese Band Otoboke Beaver Rock Your Socks Off|website=The FADER}}</ref> ''[[Stereogum]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stereogum.com/1984127/otoboke-beaver-anata-watashi-daita-ato-yome-no-meshi/premiere/|title=Otoboke Beaver \u2013 \u201cAnata Watashi Daita Ato Yome No Meshi\u201d|date=22 February 2018|publisher=}}</ref> ''[[i-D]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://i-d.vice.com/en_us/article/vbdgmy/otoboke-beaver-the-all-female-japanese-punk-band-named-after-a-love-hotel|title=otoboke beaver, the all-female japanese punk band named after a love hotel|first=Ilana|last=Kaplan|date=14 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref> and ''[[Fujirock|Fujirock Express]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fujirockexpress.net/17e/p_253|title=otobokebeaver|first=|last=FUJIROCKERS.ORG|publisher=}}</ref> In 2017 they were nominated for as Best Live Act at the AIM Independent Music Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blog.songkick.com/aim-best-live-act-2017-d3a083b0bc0c|title=Vote for Your Favorite Live Act of 2017|first=|last=Songkick|date=14 June 2017|website=Songkick}}</ref> They are  featured regularly on BBC6 radio.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/artists/45de883b-cfb6-42c0-bb9a-cfb86e27a18f|title=Otoboke Beaver - New Songs, Playlists & Latest News - BBC Music|website=BBC}}</ref> The band have also received many positive accolades/mentions from peers including [[Emi Morimoto]] of [[Shonen Knife]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.themazerocks.com/gig/shonen-knife-jap-bruja|title=Damnably Presents...SHONEN KNIFE (Jap) + Otoboke Beaver (Jap) + Leggy (USA) + Bruja (UK) **SOLD OUT** - The Maze, Live Music Venue, Nottingham|publisher=}}</ref> [[Tadanobu Asano|Tadanobu Asano,]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/otobokebeaver/status/1007914775676764160|title=\u305d\u3057\u3066\u3001SODA!\u306e\u6d45\u91ce\u5fe0\u4fe1\u3055\u307e\u304c \u304a\u3068\u30d3\u301c\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6\u3092\u307f\u306b\u304d\u3066\u304f\u308c\u3066\u3044\u307e\u3057\u305f\u2026\u81ea\u6162\u3057\u3061\u3083\u3046\u305e\u301cpic.twitter.com/rDt02AxczB|first=|last=\u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\uff5e\u30d0\uff5e|date=16 June 2018|publisher=}}</ref> [[The Cribs]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/thecribs/status/997073340161449984|title=Otoboke Beaver. Punk-as-fuck.pic.twitter.com/J4Ev9sWZyy|first=The|last=Cribs|date=17 May 2018|publisher=}}</ref> [[Mat Osman]] of [[Suede (band)|Suede]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/matosman/status/731063292274282497|title=How can you not love a band with a track called \"What do you mean you have talk to me at this late date?\" (1.54) ?  @otobokebeaver|first=Mat|last=Osman|date=13 May 2016|publisher=}}</ref> [[Paul Thomson]] of [[Franz Ferdinand (band)|Franz Ferdinand]],<ref>[https://twitter.com/pabsdebussy/status/859701966485807105 ]{{dead link|date=May 2019}}</ref> and [[Lars Ulrich]] of [[Metallica]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/at/curator/its-electric/1218413400?l=en|title=It's Electric! on Apple Music|website=Apple\u00a0Music}}</ref>\n\n==Members==\n'''Current members'''\n*Accorinrin \u2013 vocals, occasional rhythm guitar (2009\u2013present)\n*Yoyoyoshie \u2013 guitar, backing vocals (2009\u2013present)\n*Hiro-Chan \u2013 bass, backing vocals (2013\u2013present)\n*Kahokiss \u2013 drums, backing vocals (2018\u2013present)\n'''Former members'''\n*Nishikawachi \u2013 bass, backing vocals (2009\u20132013)\n*Pop \u2013 drums, backing vocals (2009\u20132018)\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Albums===\n*\u3042\u306a\u305f\u306e\u611b\u3067\u6e80\u5ba4\u4e2d | ''Anata No Ai De Manshitsu-ch\u016b'' (demo, 2011)\n*\u4eca\u591c\u9650\u308a\u306a\u3093\u3066\u7d76\u5bfe\u307b\u3093\u3068\u306b\u8a00\u308f\u305b\u306a\u3044\u3063! | ''Konya Kagiri Nante Zettai Honto ni Iwasenai!'' (EP, 2011)\n*''Present Progressive Form #002'' (live, 2012)\n*''Love Me Sign'' (EP, 2013)\n*''Okoshiyasu!! Otoboke Beaver'' (compilation, 2016)\n*''Bakuro Book'' (EP, 2016)\n*''Love Is Short!!'' (EP, 2017)\n*''Okoshiyasu!! Otoboke Beaver'' (remastered version, 2018)\n*''[[Itekoma Hits]]'' (2019)\n\n===Singles===\n*\u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\uff5e\u30d0\uff5e\u5927\u4e8b\u4ef6\u7c3f | \"Otobokebeaver Daijikenbo\" (2013)\n*\"Akimahenka\" (2015)\n*\"Si'l Vous Plait\" (2017) [Split Single w/ Say Sue Me]\n*\"Anata Watashi Daita Ato Yome No Meshi\" (2018)\n*\"Yobantoite Mojo\" (2019)\n\n===Videos===\n*\"S'il Vous Plait\" (2017)\n*\"Love Is Short!\" (2017)\n*\"Mean\" (2017)\n*\"Anata Watashi Daita Ato Yome No Meshi\" (2019)\n*\u8131\u30fb\u65e5\u9670\u306e\u5973 | \"Datsu, Hikage no Onna\" (2019, directed by Haruka Mitani<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stereogum.com/2039452/otoboke-beaver-datsu-hikage-no-onna-video/video/|title=Otoboke Beaver - \"datsu, hikage no onna\" Video|date=11 April 2019|publisher=}}</ref>)\n*\"Don't Light My Fire\" (2019)\n*\"Dirty Old Fart Is Waiting For My Reaction\" (2020)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Japanese punk rock groups]]\n{{authority control}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name                = Otoboke Beaver<br />\u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\uff5e\u30d0\uff5e\n| image               = OtobokeBeaverNottinghamLive.jpg\n| caption             = Otoboke Beaver performing in Nottingham, 2016 (L-R: Hiro-Chan, Accorinrin, Pop [on drums], Yoyoyoshie)\n| image_size          =\n| background          = group_or_band\n| alias               =\n| origin              = [[Kyoto prefecture|Kyoto]], Japan\n| genre               = {{hlist|[[Hardcore punk]]|[[noise rock]]|[[alternative rock]]}}\n| years_active        = 2009&ndash;present\n| label               = [[Damnably]]\n| associated_acts     = \n| website             = https://otobokebeaver-kyoto.jimdo.com/\n| current_members     = Accorinrin<br />Yoyoyoshie<br />Hiro-Chan<br />Kahokiss\n| past_members        = Nishikawachi<br />Pop\n}}\n\n'''Otoboke Beaver''' (\u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\uff5e\u30d0\uff5e) is a [[punk rock]] band from [[Kyoto]], Japan. The band is named after a [[love hotel]] in [[Osaka]] near the high school of one of the band members.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mcmcomiccon.com|title=Our Websites|first=MCM Comic|last=Con|website=MCM Comic Con}}</ref> Musically, the band play a very fast-paced and aggressive style of punk-rock, with frequent changes in rhythm and tempo, accompanied by [[gang vocals]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vDzecXYy1D0|title=Otoboke Beaver \u2013 Okoshiyasu!! Otoboke Beaver [FULL ALBUM STREAM]|first=|last=Damnably|date=5 June 2016|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://louderthanwar.com/otoboke-beaver-pre-tour-interview-ep-review/|title=Otoboke Beaver - pre-tour interview and EP review|date=11 April 2016|publisher=}}</ref> Their songs feature love and relationships as regular themes, often based on singer Accorinrin's own experiences.<ref name=\"auto\"/><ref name=\"electricbloomwebzine.com\">[https://www.electricbloomwebzine.com/2016/05/otoboke-beaver-interview.html ]{{dead link|date=May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe band formed in 2009 while the members were active in the \"Rock Commune\" music club at [[Ritsumeikan University]] in [[Kyoto]].<ref>\n{{cite web|url=https://rooftop.cc/interview/190807130000.php|title=\u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\u301c\u30d0\u301c - \u5727\u5dfb\u306e\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6\u3067\u4e16\u754c\u3092\u9a5a\u304b\u305b\u308b\u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\u301c\u30d0\u301c\u3001\u307e\u3060\u307e\u3060\u9032\u5316\u4e2d\uff01 - \u30a4\u30f3\u30bf\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc (Band Interview in Japanese) - Rooftop Aug. 8, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.damnably.com/otoboke-beaver-%e3%81%8a%e3%81%a8%e3%81%bc%e3%81%91%e3%83%93%ef%bd%9e%e3%83%90%ef%bd%9e/|title=Otoboke Beaver - Damnably|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"electricbloomwebzine.com\"/> The original members were Accorinrin (guitar, vocals), Yoyoyoshie (guitar), Pop (drums), and Nishikawachi (bass). \n\nIn June 2011, Otoboke Beaver released a demo CD featuring three songs, including an early version of \"Chuchu Song,\" a live favorite that would be later re-recorded and distributed to supporters who helped fund the band's first trip to the United States. A mini-album followed in December of the same year. The cover art for both releases were designed by Yukari Matsuoka, and feature a distinctive cartoon of a nude woman with a rabbit's head.{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\nIn 2012 the group released their first live album through Egypt Records. In 2013 they released a limited-edition single through Jet Set Records, featuring the newly recorded \"Otobokebeaver Daijikenbo\" and two live tracks. In March of the same year, the band released the mini-album, ''Love Me Sign''. Bassist Nishikawachi left the band in 2013 and was replaced by Hiro-Chan, a fan who asked to join via e-mail.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://otobokebeaver-kyoto.jimdo.com/biography/|title=\ud83d\udc6f We Are Otoboke Beaver \ud83d\udc6f|website=Otoboke Beaver official web site}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.list.co.uk/article/89648-interview-otoboke-beaver-people-in-japan-perform-feelings-without-moving-bodies-but-people-in-uk-tell-us-directly/|title=Interview: Otoboke Beaver \u2013 'People in Japan perform feelings without moving bodies. But people in UK tell us directly.'|date=21 March 2017|website=The List}}</ref> \n\nOtoboke Beaver participated in [[Record Store Day|Record Store Day 2015]], releasing the single  \"Akimahenka\" on vinyl. In 2016, the band signed with UK-based label [[Damnably]]. The ''Okoshiyasu!! Otoboke Beaver'' compilation album was released, featuring the majority of the songs found on the group's first two mini-albums, with the addition of \"Akimahenka.\" The band recorded a live session for John Kennedy on [[XFM]] and toured the UK with [[Shonen Knife]] and Leggy. The EP ''Bakuro Book'' followed shortly thereafter, with another EP titled ''Love is Short!!'' appearing the following year for [[Record Store Day|Record Store Day 2017]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://otobokebeaver-kyoto.jimdo.com/discography/|title=\ud83d\udc6fDISCOGRAPHY\ud83d\udc6f|website=Otoboke Beaver official web site}}</ref> The song \"Love Is Short!!\" reached the UK singles chart.{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\nThe band began touring internationally in 2016, including dates at the 100 Club in London and [[South by Southwest|SXSW]] in the United States in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://schedule.sxsw.com/2017/events/MS37763|title=Otoboke Beaver \u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\uff5e\u30d0\uff5e|website=SXSW 2019 Schedule}}</ref> Their trip to SXSW was helped by fan-funding via Campfire and [[Kickstarter]] in order to help cover travel expenses.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://damnably.bandcamp.com/track/otoboke-beaver-chu-chu-song|title=Otoboke Beaver - Chu Chu Song, by Damnably|website=Damnably}}</ref> In 2018, the band traveled over 24,000 miles in one week to play two slots at the [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival|Coachella Festival]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fuse.tv/2018/01/coachella-2018-x-japan-otoboke-beaver-japanese-rock-diversity|title=Coachella 2018 Spotlights J-Rock With X Japan and Otoboke Beaver|first=|last=News|website=Fuse}}</ref> and a three-date headlining tour in the UK with label-mates [[Say Sue Me]] and Leggy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.damnably.com/2017/12/attyuuma-blink-of-an-eye-2018-tour-%e3%81%8a%e3%81%a8%e3%81%bc%e3%81%91%e3%83%93%ef%bd%9e%e3%83%90%ef%bd%9e%e3%80%80-otoboke-beaver-kyoto-japan-w-say-sue-me-busan-south-korea/|title=ATTYUUMA (Blink of an eye) 2018 Tour \u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\uff5e\u30d0\uff5e - Otoboke Beaver (Kyoto, Japan) w/ Say Sue Me (Busan, South Korea) & Leggy (USA) - Damnably|publisher=}}</ref> Other notable tour-mates have included [[The Cribs]], [[Miyavi]], [[Guitar Wolf]], and [[Wussy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.synclinks.co.uk/artist/ODIxNjgtMzdiNjZk/|title=Bucks Music Group - Otoboke Beaver|website=www.synclinks.co.uk}}</ref>\n\nThe album ''Okoshiyasu!! Otoboke Beaver'' was re-released on vinyl for [[Record Store Day]] in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://recordstoreday.co.uk/releases/rsd-2018/otoboke-beaver/|title=Otoboke Beaver - Record Store Day|website=recordstoreday.co.uk}}</ref> Also that year, founding drummer Pop announced her departure from the band.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://otobokebeaver.kyotolog.net/%E6%9C%AA%E9%81%B8%E6%8A%9E/%E3%81%8A%E3%81%A8%E3%81%BC%E3%81%91%E3%83%93%EF%BD%9E%E3%83%90%EF%BD%9E%E3%82%92%E5%BF%9C%E6%8F%B4%E3%81%97%E3%81%A6%E3%81%8F%E3%81%A0%E3%81%95%E3%81%A3%E3%81%A6%E3%81%84%E3%82%8B%E7%9A%86%E6%A7%98%E3%81%B8|title=\u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\uff5e\u30d0\uff5e\u306e\u304a\u3078\u3084 \u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\uff5e\u30d0\uff5e\u3092\u5fdc\u63f4\u3057\u3066\u304f\u3060\u3055\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u7686\u69d8\u3078|website=otobokebeaver.kyotolog.net}}</ref> Pop was replaced by Kahokiss, who had attended the same university music club as the band's founding members almost a decade before. In March 2019, Otoboke Beaver performed at SXSW in Austin, Texas.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://schedule.sxsw.com/2019/artists/2004502|title=Otoboke Beaver|website=SXSW 2019 Schedule|language=en|access-date=2019-03-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://jrock247.com/2019/02/asterism-ex-girl-otoboke-beaver-among-top-japanese-indie-acts-sxsw-2019/|title=ASTERISM, eX-GIRL, Otoboke Beaver among top Japanese indie acts at SXSW 2019|date=2019-02-21|website=JRock247|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-16}}</ref> The album ''[[Itekoma Hits]]'', featuring new songs and compiling some previously-released singles, was released by Damnably in April 2019.\n\n==Response==\nOtoboke Beaver's fun yet frenetic sound and raucous live performances have garnered them praise from the likes of ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/19162-otoboke-beaver-love-is-short/|title=Listen to 'Love Is Short' by Otoboke Beaver|publisher=|via=pitchfork.com}}</ref> [[NPR]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2017/04/21/524864227/japanese-punks-otoboke-beaver-take-revenge-in-a-grindhouse-inspired-video|title=Japanese Punks Otoboke Beaver Take Revenge In A Grindhouse-Inspired Video|website=NPR.org}}</ref> [[The Fader|The Fader,]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2017/03/29/otoboke-beaver-sil-vous-plait-video|title=Watch Outrageously Cool Japanese Band Otoboke Beaver Rock Your Socks Off|website=The FADER}}</ref> ''[[Stereogum]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stereogum.com/1984127/otoboke-beaver-anata-watashi-daita-ato-yome-no-meshi/premiere/|title=Otoboke Beaver \u2013 \u201cAnata Watashi Daita Ato Yome No Meshi\u201d|date=22 February 2018|publisher=}}</ref> ''[[i-D]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://i-d.vice.com/en_us/article/vbdgmy/otoboke-beaver-the-all-female-japanese-punk-band-named-after-a-love-hotel|title=otoboke beaver, the all-female japanese punk band named after a love hotel|first=Ilana|last=Kaplan|date=14 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref> and ''[[Fujirock|Fujirock Express]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fujirockexpress.net/17e/p_253|title=otobokebeaver|first=|last=FUJIROCKERS.ORG|publisher=}}</ref> In 2017 they were nominated for as Best Live Act at the AIM Independent Music Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blog.songkick.com/aim-best-live-act-2017-d3a083b0bc0c|title=Vote for Your Favorite Live Act of 2017|first=|last=Songkick|date=14 June 2017|website=Songkick}}</ref> They are  featured regularly on BBC6 radio.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/artists/45de883b-cfb6-42c0-bb9a-cfb86e27a18f|title=Otoboke Beaver - New Songs, Playlists & Latest News - BBC Music|website=BBC}}</ref> The band have also received many positive accolades/mentions from peers including [[Emi Morimoto]] of [[Shonen Knife]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.themazerocks.com/gig/shonen-knife-jap-bruja|title=Damnably Presents...SHONEN KNIFE (Jap) + Otoboke Beaver (Jap) + Leggy (USA) + Bruja (UK) **SOLD OUT** - The Maze, Live Music Venue, Nottingham|publisher=}}</ref> [[Tadanobu Asano|Tadanobu Asano,]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/otobokebeaver/status/1007914775676764160|title=\u305d\u3057\u3066\u3001SODA!\u306e\u6d45\u91ce\u5fe0\u4fe1\u3055\u307e\u304c \u304a\u3068\u30d3\u301c\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6\u3092\u307f\u306b\u304d\u3066\u304f\u308c\u3066\u3044\u307e\u3057\u305f\u2026\u81ea\u6162\u3057\u3061\u3083\u3046\u305e\u301cpic.twitter.com/rDt02AxczB|first=|last=\u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\uff5e\u30d0\uff5e|date=16 June 2018|publisher=}}</ref> [[The Cribs]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/thecribs/status/997073340161449984|title=Otoboke Beaver. Punk-as-fuck.pic.twitter.com/J4Ev9sWZyy|first=The|last=Cribs|date=17 May 2018|publisher=}}</ref> [[Mat Osman]] of [[Suede (band)|Suede]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/matosman/status/731063292274282497|title=How can you not love a band with a track called \"What do you mean you have talk to me at this late date?\" (1.54) ?  @otobokebeaver|first=Mat|last=Osman|date=13 May 2016|publisher=}}</ref> [[Paul Thomson]] of [[Franz Ferdinand (band)|Franz Ferdinand]],<ref>[https://twitter.com/pabsdebussy/status/859701966485807105 ]{{dead link|date=May 2019}}</ref> and [[Lars Ulrich]] of [[Metallica]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/at/curator/its-electric/1218413400?l=en|title=It's Electric! on Apple Music|website=Apple\u00a0Music}}</ref>\n\n==Members==\n'''Current members'''\n*Accorinrin \u2013 vocals, occasional rhythm guitar (2009\u2013present)\n*Yoyoyoshie \u2013 guitar, backing vocals (2009\u2013present)\n*Hiro-Chan \u2013 bass, backing vocals (2013\u2013present)\n*Kahokiss \u2013 drums, backing vocals (2018\u2013present)\n'''Former members'''\n*Nishikawachi \u2013 bass, backing vocals (2009\u20132013)\n*Pop \u2013 drums, backing vocals (2009\u20132018)\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Albums===\n*\u3042\u306a\u305f\u306e\u611b\u3067\u6e80\u5ba4\u4e2d | ''Anata No Ai De Manshitsu-ch\u016b'' (demo, 2011)\n*\u4eca\u591c\u9650\u308a\u306a\u3093\u3066\u7d76\u5bfe\u307b\u3093\u3068\u306b\u8a00\u308f\u305b\u306a\u3044\u3063! | ''Konya Kagiri Nante Zettai Honto ni Iwasenai!'' (EP, 2011)\n*''Present Progressive Form #002'' (live, 2012)\n*''Love Me Sign'' (EP, 2013)\n*''Okoshiyasu!! Otoboke Beaver'' (compilation, 2016)\n*''Bakuro Book'' (EP, 2016)\n*''Love Is Short!!'' (EP, 2017)\n*''Okoshiyasu!! Otoboke Beaver'' (remastered version, 2018)\n*''[[Itekoma Hits]]'' (2019)\n\n===Singles===\n*\u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\uff5e\u30d0\uff